59 /*
60  * tf_Allow_fixups
61  *
62  * Integration kludge.
63  * The changes for initialization of the OR_BUF were rather widespread
64  * and could not all be done at the same time.
65  * This will be OFF until we're sure all the OR_BUF usages are initialized.
66  *
67  * Note, after this gets checked in, and is shown to work well enough, this
68  * variable can be removed, it is only retained to allow for a quick disable
69  * in the event that something ugly happens.
70  */
71 int tf_Allow_fixups = 1;

74 /*
75  * OR_TEMPOID
76  * Information about a temporary OID encountered during a transformation.
77  * These will get stuck onto the LC_OIDMAP structures as they are created
78  * for the LC_OIDSET being maintained inside the OR_FIXUP structure, whew.
79  * LC_OIDSET is a structure that gets sent accross the client/server
80  * boundary so it contains only server safe things. Unfortuantely, we
81  * need to map entries in the LC_OIDSET universe back into the DB_OBJECT*
82  * and transformation buffer locations that need to get fixed once the
83  * permanent OID is known. Rather than keep parallel structures for this,
84  * we're allowed to stick a client/side structure on each LC_OIDMAP
85  * entry, this is it.
86  * When the LC_OIDMAP is returned by the server with permanent OIDs, it
87  * will be unpacked INTO an EXISTING LC_OIDMAP structure rather than
88  * creating a new one. This existing structure will still have pointers
89  * to this structure so once the server has filled in the permanent OIDs
90  * we can simply walk over the LC_OIDMAP, get into the OR_TEMPOID and make
91  * the appropriate modifications.
92  */
93 typedef struct or_tempoid
94 {
95 
96  int refsize; /* number of elements in array */
97  int refcount; /* our fill pointer */
98  void **references; /* references, NULL terminated */
99 
100 } OR_TEMPOID;
101 
102 /*
103  * OR_FIXUP
104  * State structure maintained in an OR_BUF that encapuslates a history
105  * of temporary OIDs that we encounter during transformation.
106  * Now that the LC_OIDSET is sufficiently complex, we could just replace
107  * OR_FIXUP with that, but lets keep the encapsulation for awhile in case
108  * we need to add somethign else here.
109  */
110 typedef struct or_fixup
111 {
112  LC_OIDSET *oidset;
113 } OR_FIXUP;

209 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
210 /*
211  * tf_find_temporary_oids - walks over the memory representation of an
212  * instance and finds all the temporary OIDs within it and adds them to the
213  * oidset.
214  * return: NO_ERROR if successful, error code otherwise
215  * oidset(out): oidset to populate
216  * classobj(in): object to examine
217  */
218 int
219 tf_find_temporary_oids (LC_OIDSET * oidset, MOBJ classobj, MOBJ obj)
220 {
221  int error = NO_ERROR;
222  SM_CLASS *class_;
223  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
224  DB_TYPE type;
225  SETOBJ *col;
226 
227  /*
228  * Do this only for instance objects. This means that class objects
229  * with temporary oids in, say, class variables won't get flushed at
230  * this time, but that's probably ok. They'll get flushed as part of
231  * the ordinary class object packing business, and since they ought to
232  * be few in number, that shouldn't have much of an impact.
233  */
234  if ((classobj != (MOBJ) (&sm_Root_class)) && (obj != NULL))
235  {
236 
237  class_ = (SM_CLASS *) classobj;
238 
239  for (att = class_->attributes; att != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; att = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) att->header.next)
240  {
241 
242  type = TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (att->domain);
243  if (type == DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
244  {
245  WS_MEMOID *mem;
246  OID *oid;
247  mem = (WS_MEMOID *) (obj + att->offset);
248  oid = &mem->oid;
249 
250  if (OID_ISTEMP (oid) && mem->pointer != NULL && !WS_IS_DELETED (mem->pointer))
251  {
252 
253  /* Make sure the ws_memoid mop is temporary. */
254  if (OID_ISTEMP (WS_OID (mem->pointer)))
255  {
256 
257  /* its an undeleted temporary object, promote */
258  if (locator_add_oidset_object (oidset, mem->pointer) == NULL)
259  {
260  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
261  error = er_errid ();
262  }
263  }
264  }
265  }
266  else if (TP_IS_SET_TYPE (type))
267  {
268  col = *(SETOBJ **) (obj + att->offset);
269 
270  error = setobj_find_temporary_oids (col, oidset);
271  }
272  }
273  }
274 
275  return error;
276 }
277 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */

279 /*
280  * optimize_sets - Called before the transformation begins to ensure that
281  * any sets this object contains are sorted before sending them to disk.
282  * return: NO_ERROR if successful, error code otherwise
283  * class(in): class structure
284  * obj(in/out): object attributes
285  * Note:
286  * In practice, sets will be unsorted only if they contained temporary
287  * OIDs at one time in their lives. This will have the side effect
288  * of doing a bulk OID assignment for each set that is unsorted and then
289  * sorting the set. This may add some time to the flush process but
290  * the sort will not allocate very much memory so it should be safe in low
291  * memory situations.
292  *
293  * This would be more effecient if we split this into two opeations,
294  * the first would walk over the entire object upgrading all temporary
295  * OIDs to permanent ones. The second sorted the sets.
296  * This would result in one batch OID assignment calls rather than
297  * one for each set. Unfortuantely, that's a little more complicated as
298  * it requires some new traversal code. Someday . . .
299  */
300 static int
301 optimize_sets (SM_CLASS * class_, MOBJ volatile obj)
302 {
303  int error = NO_ERROR;
304  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
305  SETOBJ *col;
306 
307  for (att = class_->attributes; att != NULL && error == NO_ERROR; att = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) att->header.next)
308  {
309  if (TP_IS_SET_TYPE (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (att->domain)))
310  {
311  col = *((SETOBJ **) (obj + att->offset));
312 
313  if (col)
314  {
315  /*
316  * col now has the collection pointer.
317  * sort it before we flush. The sort operation will produce
318  * batched permanent oid's on demand if needed.
319  */
320  error = setobj_sort (col);
321  }
322  }
323  }
324  return error;
325 }

328 /*
329  * tf_make_fixup - This initializes a new transformer fixup structure for use.
330  * return: fixup structure
331  * Note:
332  * It doesn't actually allocate the LC_OIDSET until we find that
333  * we have references.
334  */
335 static OR_FIXUP *
336 tf_make_fixup (void)
337 {
338  OR_FIXUP *fix;
339 
340  fix = (OR_FIXUP *) malloc (sizeof (OR_FIXUP));
341  if (fix != NULL)
342  {
343  fix->oidset = NULL;
344  }
345  return fix;
346 }

348 
349 /*
350  * tf_free_fixup - frees a fixup structure create by tf_make_fixup.
351  * return: none
352  * fix(out): fixup structure
353  * Note:
354  * This now consists of a single LC_OIDSET structure with
355  * OR_TEMPOID structure embedded within it.
356  * Since locator_free_oid_set doesn't know anything about our appendages,
357  * we have to walk the LC_OIDSET and free them first.
358  *
359  */
360 static void
361 tf_free_fixup (OR_FIXUP * fix)
362 {
363  LC_CLASS_OIDSET *class_;
364  LC_OIDMAP *oid;
365  OR_TEMPOID *temp;
366 
367  if (fix == NULL)
368  {
369  return;
370  }
371 
372  if (fix->oidset == NULL)
373  {
374  free_and_init (fix);
375  return;
376  }
377  /* free our OR_TEMPOID warts */
378  for (class_ = fix->oidset->classes; class_ != NULL; class_ = class_->next)
379  {
380  for (oid = class_->oids; oid != NULL; oid = oid->next)
381  {
382  if (oid->client_data)
383  {
384  temp = (OR_TEMPOID *) oid->client_data;
385  free_and_init (temp->references);
386  free_and_init (temp);
387  oid->client_data = NULL;
388  }
389  }
390  }
391 
392  /* now free the LC_OIDSET hierarchy */
393  locator_free_oid_set (NULL, fix->oidset);
394  free_and_init (fix);
395 }

399 #define TF_FIXUP_REFERENCE_QUANT 32
400 /*
401  * tf_add_fixup - This adds a fixup "relocation" entry for a temporary OID
402  * that's been encountered.
403  * return: error
404  * fix(in/out): fixup state
405  * obj(in): object with temporary OID
406  * ref(in): address of packed reference
407  */
408 static int
409 tf_add_fixup (OR_FIXUP * fix, DB_OBJECT * obj, void *ref)
410 {
411  LC_OIDMAP *o;
412  OR_TEMPOID *t;
413  size_t buf_size;
414 
415  /* get the oidset we're building */
416  if (fix->oidset == NULL)
417  {
418  fix->oidset = locator_make_oid_set ();
419  if (fix->oidset == NULL)
420  {
421  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
422  return er_errid ();
423  }
424  }
425 
426  o = locator_add_oidset_object (fix->oidset, obj);
427  if (o == NULL)
428  {
429  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
430  return er_errid ();
431  }
432 
433  /* check our references list */
434  t = (OR_TEMPOID *) o->client_data;
435  if (t == NULL)
436  {
437  /* this is a new OID, add our reference wart */
438  t = (OR_TEMPOID *) malloc (sizeof (OR_TEMPOID));
439  if (t == NULL)
440  {
441  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (OR_TEMPOID));
442  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
443  }
444 
445  buf_size = sizeof (void *) * TF_FIXUP_REFERENCE_QUANT;
446  t->references = (void **) malloc (buf_size);
447  if (t->references == NULL)
448  {
449  free_and_init (t);
450 
451  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, buf_size);
452  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
453  }
454  t->refsize = TF_FIXUP_REFERENCE_QUANT;
455  t->references[0] = ref;
456  t->refcount = 1;
457  o->client_data = (void *) t;
458  }
459  else
460  {
461  /* we've already had at least one reference, add another one */
462  if (t->refcount >= t->refsize)
463  {
464  /* its time to grow */
465  t->refsize = t->refcount + TF_FIXUP_REFERENCE_QUANT;
466  buf_size = t->refsize * sizeof (void *);
467  t->references = (void **) realloc (t->references, buf_size);
468  if (t->references == NULL)
469  {
470  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, buf_size);
471  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
472  }
473  }
474  t->references[t->refcount] = ref;
475  t->refcount++;
476  }
477 
478  return NO_ERROR;
479 }

482 /*
483  * tf_need_permanent_oid - called when a temporary OID is encountered during
484  * various packing places to ensure permanent oid assignment
485  * return: oid to store
486  * buf(in/out): packing buffer
487  * obj(in): object to examine
488  * Note:
489  * This is called by the various packing functions when they encounter
490  * a temporary OID that needs to be packed. If this is an INSTANCE OID,
491  * and we're maintaining a deferred "fixup" buffer, then we return a NULL
492  * oid and add an entry to the fixup state.
493  *
494  * If this is a CLASS OID, or if we're not maintaining a fixup buffer,
495  * then we simply call locator_assign_permanent_oid to immeidately get a
496  * permanent OID.
497  *
498  * The oid returned by this function does not need to be freed but it
499  * must be used or copied immediately.
500  *
501  * NULL is returned on error.
502  */
503 OID *
504 tf_need_permanent_oid (OR_BUF * buf, DB_OBJECT * obj)
505 {
506  OID *oidp;
507 
508  oidp = NULL;
509 
510  /*
511  * if we have a fixup buffer, and this is NOT a class object, then make
512  * an entry for it.
513  */
514  if (tf_Allow_fixups && buf->fixups != NULL && obj->class_mop != NULL && obj->class_mop != sm_Root_class_mop)
515  {
516 
517  if (tf_add_fixup (buf->fixups, obj, buf->ptr) != NO_ERROR)
518  {
519  or_abort (buf);
520  }
521  else
522  {
523  /* leave the NULL oid in the buffer until we can fix it */
524  oidp = (OID *) (&oid_Null_oid);
525  }
526  }
527  else
528  {
529  /*
530  * couldn't make a fixup buffer entry, go to the server and assign
531  * it in the usual way.
532  */
533  if (locator_assign_permanent_oid (obj) == NULL)
534  {
535  /* this is serious */
536  or_abort (buf);
537  }
538  else
539  {
540  oidp = WS_OID (obj);
541  }
542  }
543  return oidp;
544 }

547 /*
548  * fixup_callback - LC_OIDMAP_CALLBACK function passed to locator_assign_oidset
549  * by tf_do_fixup function.
550  * return: none
551  * oidmap(in): oidmap being processed
552  * Note:
553  * This function gets called for each oid that has been made permanent,
554  * here we get our client appendage out of the client_data field, then
555  * whip through the references list so that they can be properly updated.
556  */
557 static void
558 fixup_callback (LC_OIDMAP * oidmap)
559 {
560  OR_TEMPOID *t;
561  int i;
562 
563  t = (OR_TEMPOID *) oidmap->client_data;
564  if (t != NULL)
565  {
566  /* fix the packed references */
567  for (i = 0; i < t->refcount; i++)
568  {
569  OR_PUT_OID (t->references[i], &(oidmap->oid));
570  }
571  }
572 }

575 /*
576  * tf_do_fixup - Process the fixup operations left over after a transformation.
577  * return: error code
578  * fix(): fixup state
579  */
580 static int
581 tf_do_fixup (OR_FIXUP * fix)
582 {
583  int error = NO_ERROR;
584 
585  if (fix != NULL && fix->oidset != NULL)
586  {
587  error = locator_assign_oidset (fix->oidset, fixup_callback);
588  }
589 
590  return error;
591 }

594 /*
595  * put_varinfo - Write the variable attribute offset table for an instance.
596  * return: NO_ERROR
597  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
598  * obj(in): instance memory
599  * class(in): class of instance
600  */
601 static int
602 put_varinfo (OR_BUF * buf, char *obj, SM_CLASS * class_, int offset_size)
603 {
604  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
605  char *mem;
606  int a, offset, len;
607  int rc = NO_ERROR;
608 
609  if (class_->variable_count)
610  {
611  /* compute the variable offsets relative to the end of the header (beginning of variable table) */
612  offset =
613  OR_VAR_TABLE_SIZE_INTERNAL (class_->variable_count,
614  offset_size) + class_->fixed_size + OR_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (class_->fixed_count);
615 
616  for (a = class_->fixed_count; a < class_->att_count; a++)
617  {
618  att = &class_->attributes[a];
619  mem = obj + att->offset;
620 
621  if (att->domain->type->data_lengthmem != NULL)
622  {
623  len = (*(att->domain->type->data_lengthmem)) (mem, att->domain, 1);
624  }
625  else
626  {
627  len = att->domain->type->disksize;
628  }
629 
630  or_put_offset_internal (buf, offset, offset_size);
631  offset += len;
632  }
633 
634  or_put_offset_internal (buf, offset, offset_size);
635  buf->ptr = PTR_ALIGN (buf->ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
636  }
637  return rc;
638 }

641 /*
642  * object_size - Calculates the amount of disk storage required for an instance.
643  * return: bytes of disk storage required
644  * class(in): class structure
645  * obj(in): instance to examine
646  */
647 static int
648 object_size (SM_CLASS * class_, MOBJ obj, int *offset_size_ptr)
649 {
650  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
651  char *mem;
652  int a, size;
653 
654  *offset_size_ptr = OR_BYTE_SIZE;
655 
656 re_check:
657 
658  size = OR_MVCC_INSERT_HEADER_SIZE + class_->fixed_size + OR_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (class_->fixed_count);
659 
660  if (class_->variable_count)
661  {
662  size += OR_VAR_TABLE_SIZE_INTERNAL (class_->variable_count, *offset_size_ptr);
663  for (a = class_->fixed_count; a < class_->att_count; a++)
664  {
665  att = &class_->attributes[a];
666  mem = obj + att->offset;
667 
668  if (att->domain->type->data_lengthmem != NULL)
669  {
670  size += (*(att->domain->type->data_lengthmem)) (mem, att->domain, 1);
671  }
672  else
673  {
674  size += att->domain->type->disksize;
675  }
676  }
677  }
678 
679  if (*offset_size_ptr == OR_BYTE_SIZE && size > OR_MAX_BYTE)
680  {
681  *offset_size_ptr = OR_SHORT_SIZE; /* 2byte */
682  goto re_check;
683  }
684  if (*offset_size_ptr == OR_SHORT_SIZE && size > OR_MAX_SHORT)
685  {
686  *offset_size_ptr = BIG_VAR_OFFSET_SIZE; /* 4byte */
687  goto re_check;
688  }
689  return (size);
690 }

693 /*
694  * put_attributes - Write the fixed and variable attribute values.
695  * return: on overflow, or_overflow will call longjmp and jump to the
696  * outer caller
697  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
698  * obj(in): instance memory
699  * class(in): class structure
700  * Note:
701  * The object header and offset table will already have been written.
702  * Assumes that the schema manager is smart enough to keep the
703  * attributes in their appropriate disk ordering.
704  */
705 static int
706 put_attributes (OR_BUF * buf, char *obj, SM_CLASS * class_)
707 {
708  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
709  char *start;
710  int pad;
711 
712  /*
713  * write fixed attribute values, if unbound, leave zero or garbage
714  * it doesn't really matter.
715  */
716  start = buf->ptr;
717  for (att = class_->attributes; att != NULL && !att->type->variable_p; att = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) att->header.next)
718  {
719  PRIM_WRITE (att->type, att->domain, buf, obj + att->offset);
720  }
721 
722  /* bring the end of the fixed width block up to proper alignment */
723  pad = (int) (buf->ptr - start);
724  if (pad < class_->fixed_size)
725  {
726  or_pad (buf, class_->fixed_size - pad);
727  }
728  else if (pad > class_->fixed_size)
729  { /* mismatched fixed block calculations */
730  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_SM_CORRUPTED, 0);
731  or_abort (buf);
732  }
733 
734  /* write the bound bits */
735  if (class_->fixed_count)
736  {
737  or_put_data (buf, obj + OBJ_HEADER_BOUND_BITS_OFFSET, OR_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (class_->fixed_count));
738  }
739  /* write the variable attributes */
740 
741  for (; att != NULL; att = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) att->header.next)
742  {
743  PRIM_WRITE (att->type, att->domain, buf, obj + att->offset);
744  }
745  return NO_ERROR;
746 }

749 /*
750  * tf_mem_to_disk - Translate an instance from its memory format into the
751  * disk format.
752  * return: zero on success, non-zero on error
753  * classmop(in): class of this instance
754  * classobj(in): class structure
755  * obj(in/out): instance memory to translate
756  * record(out): destination disk record
757  * index_flag(out): set if there are indexes on any attributes
758  * Note:
759  * If there was an overflow error on the given record, we determine
760  * the required size and return this size as a negative number, otherwise
761  * a zero is returned to indicate successful translation.
762  * Note that volatile is used here to prevent the compiler from
763  * optimizing variables into registers that aren't preserved by
764  * setjmp/longjmp.
765  */
766 TF_STATUS
767 tf_mem_to_disk (MOP classmop, MOBJ classobj, MOBJ volatile obj, RECDES * record, bool * index_flag)
768 {
769  OR_BUF orep, *buf;
770  SM_CLASS *volatile class_; /* prevent register optimization */
771  int chn;
772  bool has_index = false;
773  unsigned int repid_bits;
774  TF_STATUS status;
775  volatile int expected_size;
776  volatile int offset_size;
777 
778  buf = &orep;
779  or_init (buf, record->data, record->area_size);
780  buf->error_abort = 1;
781 
782  if (tf_Allow_fixups)
783  {
784  buf->fixups = tf_make_fixup ();
785  if (buf->fixups == NULL)
786  {
787  return TF_ERROR;
788  }
789  }
790 
791  class_ = (SM_CLASS *) classobj;
792 
793  if (optimize_sets (class_, obj) != NO_ERROR)
794  {
795  if (tf_Allow_fixups)
796  {
797  tf_free_fixup (buf->fixups);
798  }
799  return TF_ERROR;
800  }
801 
802  expected_size = object_size (class_, obj, (int *) &offset_size);
803  if ((expected_size + OR_MVCC_MAX_HEADER_SIZE - OR_MVCC_INSERT_HEADER_SIZE) > record->area_size)
804  {
805  record->length = -expected_size;
806 
807  /* make sure we free this */
808  if (tf_Allow_fixups)
809  {
810  tf_free_fixup (buf->fixups);
811  }
812 
813  *index_flag = false;
814  return (TF_OUT_OF_SPACE);
815  }
816 
817  switch (_setjmp (buf->env))
818  {
819  case 0:
820  status = TF_SUCCESS;
821 
822  if (OID_ISTEMP (WS_OID (classmop)))
823  {
824  /*
825  * since this isn't a mem_oid, can't rely on write_oid to do this,
826  * don't bother making this part of the deferred fixup stuff yet.
827  */
828  if (locator_assign_permanent_oid (classmop) == NULL)
829  {
830  or_abort (buf);
831  }
832  }
833 
834  /* header */
835 
836  repid_bits = class_->repid;
837  if (class_->fixed_count)
838  {
839  repid_bits |= OR_BOUND_BIT_FLAG;
840  }
841  /* offset size */
842  OR_SET_VAR_OFFSET_SIZE (repid_bits, offset_size);
843 
844  chn = WS_CHN (obj) + 1;
845 
846  /* in most of the cases, we expect the MVCC header of a new object to have OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_INSID flag,
847  * repid_bits, MVCC insert id and chn. This header may be changed later, at insert/update. So, we must be sure
848  * that the record has enough free space. */
849 
850  repid_bits |= (OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_INSID << OR_MVCC_FLAG_SHIFT_BITS);
851  or_put_int (buf, repid_bits);
852  or_put_int (buf, chn); /* CHN, short size */
853  or_put_bigint (buf, MVCCID_NULL); /* MVCC insert id */
854 
855  /* variable info block */
856  put_varinfo (buf, obj, class_, offset_size);
857 
858  /* attributes, fixed followed by variable */
859  put_attributes (buf, obj, class_);
860 
861  record->length = (int) (buf->ptr - buf->buffer);
862 
863  /* see if there are any indexes */
864  has_index = classobj_class_has_indexes (class_);
865 
866  /*
867  * assign permanent OID's and make the necessary adjustments in
868  * the packed buffer.
869  */
870  if (tf_do_fixup (buf->fixups) != NO_ERROR)
871  {
872  status = TF_ERROR;
873  }
874 
875  /*
876  * Now that we know the object has been packed up safely, it's safe
877  * to update the coherency number of the in-memory image.
878  */
879  WS_CHN (obj) = chn;
880 
881  break;
882 
883  /* if the longjmp status was anything other than ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW, it represents an error condition and
884  * er_set will have been called */
885  case ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW:
886  status = TF_OUT_OF_SPACE;
887  record->length = -expected_size;
888  has_index = false;
889  break;
890 
891  default:
892  status = TF_ERROR;
893  has_index = false;
894  break;
895  }
896 
897  /* make sure we free this */
898  if (tf_Allow_fixups)
899  {
900  tf_free_fixup (buf->fixups);
901  }
902 
903  *index_flag = has_index;
904 
905  buf->error_abort = 0;
906  return (status);
907 }

910 /*
911  * get_current - Loads an instance from disk using the latest class
912  * representation.
913  * return: new instance memory
914  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
915  * class(): class of this instance
916  * obj_ptr(out): loaded object (same as return value)
917  * bound_bit_flag(in): initial status of bound bits
918  */
919 static char *
920 get_current (OR_BUF * buf, SM_CLASS * class_, MOBJ * obj_ptr, int bound_bit_flag, int offset_size)
921 {
922  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
923  char *obj, *mem, *start;
924  int *vars, rc = NO_ERROR;
925  int i, j, offset, offset2, pad;
926 
927  obj = NULL;
928  /* need nicer way to store these */
929  vars = NULL;
930  if (class_->variable_count)
931  {
932  vars = (int *) db_ws_alloc (sizeof (int) * class_->variable_count);
933  if (vars == NULL)
934  {
935  or_abort (buf);
936  }
937  else
938  {
939  /* get the offsets relative to the end of the header (beginning of variable table) */
940  offset = or_get_offset_internal (buf, &rc, offset_size);
941  for (i = 0; i < class_->variable_count; i++)
942  {
943  offset2 = or_get_offset_internal (buf, &rc, offset_size);
944  vars[i] = offset2 - offset;
945  offset = offset2;
946  }
947  buf->ptr = PTR_ALIGN (buf->ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
948  }
949  }
950 
951  /*
952  * if there are no bound bits on disk, allocate the instance block
953  * with all the bits turned on, we have to assume that the values
954  * are non-null
955  */
956  obj = *obj_ptr = obj_alloc (class_, (bound_bit_flag) ? 0 : 1);
957 
958  if (obj == NULL)
959  {
960  if (vars != NULL)
961  {
962  db_ws_free (vars);
963  }
964  or_abort (buf);
965  }
966  else
967  {
968  /* fixed */
969  start = buf->ptr;
970  for (i = 0; i < class_->fixed_count; i++)
971  {
972  att = &(class_->attributes[i]);
973  mem = obj + att->offset;
974  PRIM_READ (att->type, att->domain, buf, mem, -1);
975  }
976 
977  /* round up to a to the end of the fixed block */
978  pad = (int) (buf->ptr - start);
979  if (pad < class_->fixed_size)
980  {
981  or_advance (buf, class_->fixed_size - pad);
982  }
983  /* bound bits, if not present, we have to assume everything is bound */
984  if (bound_bit_flag && class_->fixed_count)
985  {
986  or_get_data (buf, obj + OBJ_HEADER_BOUND_BITS_OFFSET, OR_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (class_->fixed_count));
987  }
988 
989  /* variable */
990  if (vars != NULL)
991  {
992  for (i = class_->fixed_count, j = 0; i < class_->att_count && j < class_->variable_count; i++, j++)
993  {
994  att = &(class_->attributes[i]);
995  mem = obj + att->offset;
996  PRIM_READ (att->type, att->domain, buf, mem, vars[j]);
997  }
998  }
999  }
1000 
1001  if (vars != NULL)
1002  {
1003  db_ws_free (vars);
1004  }
1005 
1006  return (obj);
1007 }

1011  * find_current_attribute - Given an instance attribute id, find the
1012  * corresponding attribute in the latest representation.
1013  * return: pointer to current attribute. NULL if not found
1014  * class(in): class structure
1015  * id(in): attribute id
1016  */
1017 static SM_ATTRIBUTE *
1018 find_current_attribute (SM_CLASS * class_, int id)
1019 {

1021

1023  for (att = class_->attributes; att != NULL && found == NULL; att = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) att->header.next)
1024  {
1025  if (att->id == id)
1026  {
1027  found = att;
1028  }
1029  }
1030  return (found);

1034 /*
1035  * clear_new_unbound - This initializes the space created for instance
1036  * attributes that had no saved values on disk.
1037  * return: void
1038  * obj(in/out): instance memory
1039  * class(in): class of this instance
1040  * oldrep(in): old representation (of instance on disk)
1041  * Note:
1042  * This happens when an object is converted to a new representation
1043  * that had one or more attributes added.
1044  * It might be more efficient to do this for all fields when the instance
1045  * memory is first allocated ?
1046  * The original_value is used if it has a value.
1047  */
1048 static void
1049 clear_new_unbound (char *obj, SM_CLASS * class_, SM_REPRESENTATION * oldrep)
1050 {
1051  SM_ATTRIBUTE *att;
1052  SM_REPR_ATTRIBUTE *rat, *found;
1053  char *mem;
1054 
1055  for (att = class_->attributes; att != NULL; att = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) att->header.next)
1056  {
1057  found = NULL;
1058  for (rat = oldrep->attributes; rat != NULL && found == NULL; rat = rat->next)
1059  {
1060  if (rat->attid == att->id)
1061  {
1062  found = rat;
1063  }
1064  }
1065  if (found == NULL)
1066  {
1067  mem = obj + att->offset;
1068  /* initialize in case there isn't an initial value */
1069  PRIM_INITMEM (att->type, mem, att->domain);
1070  if (!DB_IS_NULL (&att->default_value.original_value))
1071  {
1072  /* assign the initial value, should check for non-existance ? */
1073  PRIM_SETMEM (att->type, att->domain, mem, &att->default_value.original_value);
1074  if (!att->type->variable_p)
1075  {
1076  OBJ_SET_BOUND_BIT (obj, att->storage_order);
1077  }
1078  }
1079  }
1080  }
1081 }

1084 /*
1085  * get_old - This creates an instance from an obsolete disk representation.
1086  * return: new instance memory
1087  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
1088  * class(in): class of this instance
1089  * obj_ptr(out): return value
1090  * repid(in): old representation id
1091  * bound_bit_flag(in): initial status of bound bits
1092  * Note:
1093  * Any new attributes that had no values on disk are given a starting
1094  * value from the "original_value" field in the class.
1095  * Values for deleted attributes are discarded.
1096  */
1097 static char *
1098 get_old (OR_BUF * buf, SM_CLASS * class_, MOBJ * obj_ptr, int repid, int bound_bit_flag, int offset_size)
1099 {
1100  SM_REPRESENTATION *oldrep;
1101  SM_REPR_ATTRIBUTE *rat;
1102  SM_ATTRIBUTE **attmap;
1103  PR_TYPE *type;
1104  char *obj, *bits, *start;
1105  int *vars = NULL, rc = NO_ERROR;
1106  int i, total, offset, offset2, bytes, att_index, padded_size, fixed_size;
1107 
1108  obj = NULL;
1109  oldrep = classobj_find_representation (class_, repid);
1110 
1111  if (oldrep == NULL)
1112  {
1113  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TF_INVALID_REPRESENTATION, 1, sm_ch_name ((MOBJ) class_));
1114  }
1115  else
1116  {
1117  /*
1118  * if there are no bound bits on disk, allocate the instance block
1119  * with all the bits turned on, we have to assume that the values
1120  * are non-null
1121  */
1122  obj = *obj_ptr = obj_alloc (class_, (bound_bit_flag) ? 0 : 1);
1123 
1124  if (obj == NULL)
1125  {
1126  or_abort (buf);
1127  }
1128  else
1129  {
1130  /*
1131  * read the variable offset table, can't we just leave this on
1132  * disk ?
1133  */
1134  vars = NULL;
1135  if (oldrep->variable_count)
1136  {
1137  vars = (int *) db_ws_alloc (sizeof (int) * oldrep->variable_count);
1138  if (vars == NULL)
1139  {
1140  or_abort (buf);
1141  return NULL;
1142  }
1143  else
1144  {
1145  /* get the offsets relative to the end of the header (beginning of variable table) */
1146  offset = or_get_offset_internal (buf, &rc, offset_size);
1147  for (i = 0; i < oldrep->variable_count; i++)
1148  {
1149  offset2 = or_get_offset_internal (buf, &rc, offset_size);
1150  vars[i] = offset2 - offset;
1151  offset = offset2;
1152  }
1153  buf->ptr = PTR_ALIGN (buf->ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
1154  }
1155  }
1156 
1157  /* calculate an attribute map */
1158  total = oldrep->fixed_count + oldrep->variable_count;
1159  attmap = NULL;
1160  if (total > 0)
1161  {
1162  attmap = (SM_ATTRIBUTE **) db_ws_alloc (sizeof (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) * total);
1163  if (attmap == NULL)
1164  {
1165  if (vars != NULL)
1166  {
1167  db_ws_free (vars);
1168  }
1169  or_abort (buf);
1170  return NULL;
1171  }
1172  else
1173  {
1174  for (rat = oldrep->attributes, i = 0; rat != NULL; rat = rat->next, i++)
1175  {
1176  attmap[i] = find_current_attribute (class_, rat->attid);
1177  }
1178  }
1179  }
1180 
1181  /* read the fixed attributes */
1182  rat = oldrep->attributes;
1183  start = buf->ptr;
1184  for (i = 0; i < oldrep->fixed_count && rat != NULL && attmap != NULL; i++, rat = rat->next)
1185  {
1186  type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (rat->typeid_);
1187  if (type == NULL)
1188  {
1189  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TF_INVALID_REPRESENTATION, 1,
1190  sm_ch_name ((MOBJ) class_));
1191 
1192  db_ws_free (attmap);
1193  if (vars != NULL)
1194  {
1195  db_ws_free (vars);
1196  }
1197 
1198  or_abort (buf);
1199  return NULL;
1200  }
1201 
1202  if (attmap[i] == NULL)
1203  {
1204  PRIM_READ (type, rat->domain, buf, NULL, -1);
1205  }
1206  else
1207  {
1208  PRIM_READ (type, rat->domain, buf, obj + attmap[i]->offset, -1);
1209  }
1210  }
1211 
1212  fixed_size = (int) (buf->ptr - start);
1213  padded_size = DB_ATT_ALIGN (fixed_size);
1214  or_advance (buf, (padded_size - fixed_size));
1215 
1216 
1217  /*
1218  * sigh, we now have to process the bound bits in much the same way
1219  * as the attributes above, it would be nice if these could be done
1220  * in parallel but we don't have the fixed size of the old
1221  * representation so we can't easily sneak the buffer pointer
1222  * forward, work on this someday
1223  */
1224 
1225  if (bound_bit_flag && oldrep->fixed_count)
1226  {
1227  bits = buf->ptr;
1228  bytes = OR_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (oldrep->fixed_count);
1229  if ((buf->ptr + bytes) > buf->endptr)
1230  {
1231  or_overflow (buf);
1232  }
1233 
1234  rat = oldrep->attributes;
1235  for (i = 0; i < oldrep->fixed_count && rat != NULL && attmap != NULL; i++, rat = rat->next)
1236  {
1237  if (attmap[i] != NULL)
1238  {
1239  if (OR_GET_BOUND_BIT (bits, i))
1240  {
1241  OBJ_SET_BOUND_BIT (obj, attmap[i]->storage_order);
1242  }
1243  }
1244  }
1245  or_advance (buf, bytes);
1246  }
1247 
1248  /* variable */
1249  if (vars != NULL)
1250  {
1251  for (i = 0; i < oldrep->variable_count && rat != NULL && attmap != NULL; i++, rat = rat->next)
1252  {
1253  type = PR_TYPE_FROM_ID (rat->typeid_);
1254  if (type == NULL)
1255  {
1256  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TF_INVALID_REPRESENTATION, 1,
1257  sm_ch_name ((MOBJ) class_));
1258 
1259  db_ws_free (attmap);
1260  db_ws_free (vars);
1261 
1262  or_abort (buf);
1263  return NULL;
1264  }
1265 
1266  att_index = oldrep->fixed_count + i;
1267  if (attmap[att_index] == NULL)
1268  {
1269  PRIM_READ (type, rat->domain, buf, NULL, vars[i]);
1270  }
1271  else
1272  {
1273  PRIM_READ (type, rat->domain, buf, obj + attmap[att_index]->offset, vars[i]);
1274  }
1275  }
1276  }
1277 
1278  /* should be optimizing this operation ! */
1279  clear_new_unbound (obj, class_, oldrep);
1280 
1281  if (attmap != NULL)
1282  {
1283  db_ws_free (attmap);
1284  }
1285  if (vars != NULL)
1286  {
1287  db_ws_free (vars);
1288  }
1289  }
1290  }
1291 
1292  return (obj);
1293 }

1295 
1296 /*
1297  * tf_disk_to_mem - Interface function for transforming the disk
1298  * representation of an instance into the memory representation.
1299  * return: MOBJ
1300  * classobj(in): class structure
1301  * record(in): disk record
1302  * convertp(in): set to non-zero if the object had to be converted from
1303  * an obsolete disk representation.
1304  * Note:
1305  * It is imperitive that garbage collection be disabled during this
1306  * operation.
1307  * This is because the structure being built may contain pointers
1308  * to MOPs but it has not itself been attached to its own MOP yet so it
1309  * doesn't serve as a gc root. Make sure the caller
1310  * calls ws_cache() immediately after we return so the new object
1311  * gets attached as soon as possible. We must also have already
1312  * allocated the MOP in the caller so that we don't get one of the
1313  * periodic gc's when we attempt to allocate a new MOP.
1314  * This dependency should be isolated in a ws_ function called by
1315  * the locator.
1316  */
1317 MOBJ
1318 tf_disk_to_mem (MOBJ classobj, RECDES * record, int *convertp)
1319 {
1320  OR_BUF orep, *buf;
1321  SM_CLASS *class_ = NULL;
1322  char *obj = NULL;
1323  unsigned int repid_bits;
1324  int repid, convert, chn, bound_bit_flag;
1325  int rc = NO_ERROR;
1326  int offset_size;
1327  char mvcc_flags;
1328 
1329  buf = &orep;
1330  or_init (buf, record->data, record->length);
1331  buf->error_abort = 1;
1332 
1333  switch (_setjmp (buf->env))
1334  {
1335  case 0:
1336  class_ = (SM_CLASS *) classobj;
1337  obj = NULL;
1338  convert = 0;
1339  /* offset size */
1340  offset_size = OR_GET_OFFSET_SIZE (buf->ptr);
1341 
1342  /* in case of MVCC, repid_bits contains MVCC flags */
1343  repid_bits = or_mvcc_get_repid_and_flags (buf, &rc);
1344  repid = repid_bits & OR_MVCC_REPID_MASK;
1345 
1346  mvcc_flags = (char) ((repid_bits >> OR_MVCC_FLAG_SHIFT_BITS) & OR_MVCC_FLAG_MASK);
1347 
1348  chn = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
1349 
1350  if (mvcc_flags & OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_INSID)
1351  {
1352  /* skip insert id */
1353  or_advance (buf, OR_MVCCID_SIZE);
1354  }
1355 
1356  if (mvcc_flags & OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_DELID)
1357  {
1358  /* skip delete id */
1359  or_advance (buf, OR_MVCCID_SIZE);
1360  }
1361 
1362  if (mvcc_flags & OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_PREV_VERSION)
1363  {
1364  /* skip prev version lsa */
1365  or_advance (buf, OR_MVCC_PREV_VERSION_LSA_SIZE);
1366  }
1367 
1368  bound_bit_flag = repid_bits & OR_BOUND_BIT_FLAG;
1369 
1370  if (repid == class_->repid)
1371  {
1372  obj = get_current (buf, class_, &obj, bound_bit_flag, offset_size);
1373  }
1374  else
1375  {
1376  obj = get_old (buf, class_, &obj, repid, bound_bit_flag, offset_size);
1377  convert = 1;
1378  }
1379 
1380  /* set the chn of the object */
1381  if (obj != NULL)
1382  {
1383  WS_CHN (obj) = chn;
1384  }
1385 
1386  *convertp = convert;
1387  break;
1388 
1389  default:
1390  /* make sure to clear the object that was being created, an appropriate error will have been set */
1391  if (obj != NULL)
1392  {
1393  obj_free_memory (class_, obj);
1394  obj = NULL;
1395  }
1396  break;
1397  }
1398 
1399  buf->error_abort = 0;
1400  return (obj);
1401 }

1590 /*
1591  * object_set_size - Calculates the disk storage required for a set of object
1592  * pointers.
1593  * return: byte size for a set of OIDs
1594  * list(in): object list
1595  */
1596 static int
1597 object_set_size (DB_OBJLIST * list)
1598 {
1599  DB_OBJLIST *l;
1600  int count, size;
1601 
1602  /* store NULL for empty set */
1603  if (list == NULL)
1604  {
1605  return 0;
1606  }
1607 
1608  size = 0;
1609  for (count = 0, l = list; l != NULL; l = l->next)
1610  {
1611  if (WS_IS_DELETED (l->op))
1612  {
1613  continue;
1614  }
1615  count++;
1616  }
1617 
1618  if (count == 0)
1619  {
1620  return 0;
1621  }
1622 
1623  size += OR_SET_HEADER_SIZE;
1624  size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* size of domain word */
1625  size += OR_INT_SIZE; /* size of the built-in object domain */
1626  size += (count * tp_Object.disksize);
1627 
1628  return (size);
1629 }

1631 /*
1632  * put_object_set - Translates a list objects into the disk represenataion of a
1633  * sequence of objects
1634  * return: on overflow, or_overflow will call longjmp and jump to the outer
1635  * caller
1636  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
1637  * list(in): object list
1638  */
1639 static int
1640 put_object_set (OR_BUF * buf, DB_OBJLIST * list)
1641 {
1642  DB_OBJLIST *l;
1643  int count;
1644 
1645  /* store NULL for empty set */
1646  if (list == NULL)
1647  return ER_FAILED;
1648 
1649  for (count = 0, l = list; l != NULL; l = l->next)
1650  {
1651  if (WS_IS_DELETED (l->op))
1652  {
1653  continue;
1654  }
1655  count++;
1656  }
1657 
1658  if (count == 0)
1659  {
1660  return NO_ERROR;
1661  }
1662 
1663  /* w/ domain, no bound bits, no offsets, no tags, no substructure header */
1664  or_put_set_header (buf, DB_TYPE_SEQUENCE, count, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0);
1665 
1666  /* use the generic "object" domain */
1667  or_put_int (buf, OR_INT_SIZE); /* size of the domain */
1668  or_put_domain (buf, &tp_Object_domain, 0, 0); /* actual domain */
1669 
1670  /* should be using something other than pr_write_mop here ! */
1671  for (l = list; l != NULL; l = l->next)
1672  {
1673  if (WS_IS_DELETED (l->op))
1674  {
1675  continue;
1676  }
1677  pr_write_mop (buf, l->op);
1678  }
1679 
1680  return NO_ERROR;
1681 }

1683 /*
1684  * get_object_set - Extracts a sequence of objects in a disk representation
1685  * and converts it into an object list in memory.
1686  * return: object list NOTE: a jmp_buf has previously been established.
1687  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
1688  * expected(in): expected length

1690 static DB_OBJLIST *
1691 get_object_set (OR_BUF * buf, int expected)
1692 {

1694  MOP op;

1696  int count, i;

1699  if (expected == 0)
1700  {
1701  return NULL;
1702  }
1703 
1704  list = NULL;
1705  count = or_skip_set_header (buf);
1706  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
1707  {

1709  * Get a MOP, could assume classes mops here and make sure the resulting

1711  */

1727 /*
1728  * substructure_set_size - Calculates the disk storage for a set created from
1729  * a list of memory elements.
1730  * return: byte of disk storage required
1731  * list(in): list of elements
1732  * function(in): function to calculate element sizes
1733  * Note:
1734  * The supplied function is used to find the size of the list elements.
1735  * Even if the list is empty, there will always be at least a set header
1736  * written to disk.
1737  */
1738 static int
1739 substructure_set_size (DB_LIST * list, LSIZER function)
1740 {
1741  DB_LIST *l;
1742  int size, count;
1743 
1744  /* store NULL for empty list */
1745  if (list == NULL)
1746  {
1747  return 0;
1748  }
1749 
1750  /* header + domain length word + domain */
1751  size = OR_SET_HEADER_SIZE + OR_INT_SIZE + OR_SUB_DOMAIN_SIZE;
1752 
1753  count = 0;
1754  for (l = list; l != NULL; l = l->next, count++)
1755  {
1756  size += (*function) (l);
1757  }
1758 
1759  if (count)
1760  {
1761  /*
1762  * we have elements to store, in that case we need to add the
1763  * common substructure header at the front and an offset table
1764  */
1765  size += OR_VAR_TABLE_SIZE (count);
1766  size += OR_SUB_HEADER_SIZE;
1767  }
1768 
1769  return (size);
1770 }

1772 /*
1773  * put_substructure_set - Write the disk representation of a substructure
1774  * set from a linked list of structures.
1775  * return: void
1776  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
1777  * list(in): substructure list
1778  * writer(in): translation function
1779  * class(in): OID of meta class for this substructure
1780  * repid(in): repid for the meta class
1781  * Note:
1782  * The supplied functions calculate the size and write the elements.
1783  * The OID/repid for the metaclass will be one of the meta classes
1784  * defined in the catalog.
1785  */
1786 static void
1787 put_substructure_set (OR_BUF * buf, DB_LIST * list, LWRITER writer, OID * class_, int repid)
1788 {
1789  DB_LIST *l;
1790  char *start;
1791  int count;
1792  char *offset_ptr;
1793 
1794  /* store NULL for empty list */
1795  if (list == NULL)
1796  {
1797  return;
1798  }
1799 
1800  count = 0;
1801  for (l = list; l != NULL; l = l->next, count++);
1802 
1803  /* with domain, no bound bits, with offsets, no tags, common sub header */
1804  start = buf->ptr;
1805  or_put_set_header (buf, DB_TYPE_SEQUENCE, count, 1, 0, 1, 0, 1);
1806 
1807  if (!count)
1808  {
1809  /* we must at least store the domain even though there will be no elements */
1810  or_put_int (buf, OR_SUB_DOMAIN_SIZE);
1811  or_put_sub_domain (buf);
1812  }
1813  else
1814  {
1815  /* begin an offset table */
1816  offset_ptr = buf->ptr;
1817  or_advance (buf, OR_VAR_TABLE_SIZE (count));
1818 
1819  /* write the domain */
1820  or_put_int (buf, OR_SUB_DOMAIN_SIZE);
1821  or_put_sub_domain (buf);
1822 
1823  /* write the common substructure header */
1824  or_put_oid (buf, class_);
1825  or_put_int (buf, repid);
1826  or_put_int (buf, 0); /* flags */
1827 
1828  /* write each substructure */
1829  for (l = list; l != NULL; l = l->next)
1830  {
1831  /* determine the offset to the this element and put it in the table */
1832  OR_PUT_OFFSET (offset_ptr, (buf->ptr - start));
1833  offset_ptr += BIG_VAR_OFFSET_SIZE;
1834  /* write the substructure */
1835  (*writer) (buf, l);
1836  }
1837  /* write the final offset */
1838  OR_PUT_OFFSET (offset_ptr, (buf->ptr - start));
1839  }
1840 }

1843  * get_substructure_set - extracts a substructure set on disk and create a
1844  * list of memory structures.
1845  * return: list of structures
1846  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
1847  * reader(in): function to read the elements

1849  * Note:

1862  }
1863 
1864  list = NULL;
1865  count = or_skip_set_header (buf);

1867  {
1868  obj = (*reader) (buf);
1869  if (obj != NULL)

1963  * return: a new property list
1964  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
1965  * expected_size(in): number of bytes on disk
1966  * Note:
1967  * This reads a property list from disk.
1968  * If either the expected size is zero, NULL is returned.
1969  * If a sequence was stored on disk but it had no elements, NULL is
1970  * returned and the empty sequence is freed. This is to handle the
1971  * case where old style class objects had an empty substructure set
1972  * stored at this position. Since these will be converted to property
1973  * lists, we can just ignore them.
1974  *
1975  * A jmp_buf has previously been established.

1978 get_property_list (OR_BUF * buf, int expected_size)

1982  int max;
1983 
1984  properties = NULL;
1985  if (expected_size)
1986  {

1988  properties = db_get_set (&value);
1989  if (properties == NULL)
1990  or_abort (buf); /* trouble allocating a handle */
1991  else
1992  {
1993  max = set_size (properties);
1994  if (!max)
1995  {
1996  /*
1997  * there is an empty sequence here, get rid of it so we don't
1998  * have to carry it around
1999  */
2000  set_free (properties);
2001  properties = NULL;
2002  }
2003  }
2004  }
2005  return (properties);

2032 /*
2033  * domain_to_disk - Translates a domain list to its disk representation.
2034  * return: void
2035  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
2036  * domain(in): domain list
2037  * Note:
2038  * Translates a domain list to its disk representation.
2039  */
2040 static void
2041 domain_to_disk (OR_BUF * buf, TP_DOMAIN * domain)
2042 {
2043  char *start;
2044  int offset;
2045  DB_VALUE schema_value;
2046 
2047  /* safe-guard : domain collation flags should only be used for execution */
2048  if (TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
2049  {
2050  assert (false);
2051  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TF_OUT_OF_SYNC, 0);
2052  }
2053

2096 /*
2097  * disk_to_domain2 - Create the memory representation for a domain list from
2098  * the disk representation.
2099  * return: domain structure
2100  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
2101  * Note:
2102  * This builds a transient domain, it is called by disk_to_domain which
2103  * just turns around and caches it.
2104  *
2105  * A jmp_buf has previously been established.
2106  */
2107 static TP_DOMAIN *
2108 disk_to_domain2 (OR_BUF * buf)
2109 {
2110  OR_VARINFO *vars;
2111  TP_DOMAIN *domain;
2112  DB_TYPE typeid_;
2113  OID oid;
2114  int rc = NO_ERROR;
2115 
2116  vars = read_var_table (buf, tf_Metaclass_domain.mc_n_variable);
2117  if (vars == NULL)
2118  {
2119  or_abort (buf);
2120  return NULL;
2121  }
2122 
2123  typeid_ = (DB_TYPE) or_get_int (buf, &rc);
2124 
2125  domain = tp_domain_new (typeid_);
2126  if (domain == NULL)
2127  {
2128  free_var_table (vars);
2129  or_abort (buf);
2130  return NULL;
2131  }
2132 
2133  domain->precision = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
2134  domain->scale = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
2135  domain->codeset = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
2136  domain->collation_id = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
2137  if (typeid_ == DB_TYPE_ENUMERATION && domain->codeset == 0)
2138  {
2139  assert (domain->collation_id == LANG_COLL_ISO_BINARY);
2140  domain->codeset = INTL_CODESET_ISO88591;
2141  }
2142  /*
2143  * Read the domain class OID without promoting it to a MOP.
2144  * Could use readval, and extract the OID out of the already swizzled
2145  * MOP too.
2146  */
2147  (*(tp_Oid.data_readmem)) (buf, &oid, NULL, -1);
2148  domain->class_oid = oid;
2149 
2150  /* swizzle the pointer, we know we're on the client here */
2151  if (!OID_ISNULL (&domain->class_oid))
2152  {
2153  domain->class_mop = ws_mop (&domain->class_oid, NULL);
2154  if (domain->class_mop == NULL)
2155  {
2156  free_var_table (vars);
2157  or_abort (buf);
2158  }
2159  }
2160  domain->setdomain = (TP_DOMAIN *) get_substructure_set (buf, (LREADER) disk_to_domain2,
2161  vars[ORC_DOMAIN_SETDOMAIN_INDEX].length);
2162  domain->enumeration.collation_id = domain->collation_id;
2163 
2164  if (get_enumeration (buf, &DOM_GET_ENUMERATION (domain), vars[ORC_DOMAIN_ENUMERATION_INDEX].length) != NO_ERROR)
2165  {
2166  free_var_table (vars);
2167  tp_domain_free (domain);
2168  or_abort (buf);
2169  return NULL;
2170  }
2171 
2172  if (vars[ORC_DOMAIN_SCHEMA_JSON_OFFSET].length > 0)
2173  {
2174  char *schema_raw;
2175  int error_code;
2176 
2177  or_get_json_schema (buf, schema_raw);
2178  if (schema_raw == NULL)
2179  {
2180  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
2181  vars[ORC_DOMAIN_SCHEMA_JSON_OFFSET].length + 1);
2182  tp_domain_free (domain);
2183  free_var_table (vars);
2184  return NULL;
2185  }
2186 
2187  error_code = db_json_load_validator (schema_raw, domain->json_validator);
2188  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2189  {
2190  assert_release (false);
2191  tp_domain_free (domain);
2192  free_var_table (vars);
2193  return NULL;
2194  }
2195  }
2196 
2197  free_var_table (vars);
2198 
2199  return (domain);
2200 }

3680  * return: void
3681  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
3682  * class(in): class structure
3683  * Note:
3684  * The writing of the offset table and the attributes was split into

3689 static void
3690 class_to_disk (OR_BUF * buf, SM_CLASS * class_)
3691 {

3714  or_abort (buf);

3716  }

4129 /*
4130  * root_to_disk - Write the disk representation of the root class.
4131  * return: void
4132  * buf(in/out): translation buffer
4133  * root(in): root class object
4134  * header_size(in): the size of header - variable in MVCC
4135  * Note:
4136  * Caller must have a setup a jmpbuf (called setjmp) to handle any errors.
4137  * Only the header part of the 'root' object is serialized. Please see comment on ROOT_CLASS definition.
4138  */
4139 static void
4140 root_to_disk (OR_BUF * buf, ROOT_CLASS * root)
4141 {
4142  char *start;
4143  int offset;
4144 
4145  start = buf->ptr - OR_NON_MVCC_HEADER_SIZE; /* header already written */
4146 
4147  /* compute the variable offsets relative to the end of the header (beginning of variable table) */
4148  offset = tf_Metaclass_root.mc_fixed_size + OR_VAR_TABLE_SIZE (tf_Metaclass_root.mc_n_variable);
4149 
4150  /* name */
4151  or_put_offset (buf, offset);
4152  offset += string_disk_size (sm_ch_name ((MOBJ) root));
4153 
4154  /* end of object */
4155  or_put_offset (buf, offset);
4156  buf->ptr = PTR_ALIGN (buf->ptr, INT_ALIGNMENT);
4157 
4158  assert (OID_ISNULL (sm_ch_rep_dir ((MOBJ) root))); /* is dummy */
4159 
4160  /* heap file id - see assumptions in comment above */
4161  or_put_int (buf, (int) root->header.ch_heap.vfid.fileid);
4162  or_put_int (buf, (int) root->header.ch_heap.vfid.volid);
4163  or_put_int (buf, (int) root->header.ch_heap.hpgid);
4164 
4165  put_string (buf, sm_ch_name ((MOBJ) root));
4166 
4167  if (start + OR_NON_MVCC_HEADER_SIZE + offset != buf->ptr)
4168  {
4169  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TF_OUT_OF_SYNC, 0);
4170  }
4171 }

4247 /*
4248  * tf_disk_to_class - transforming the disk representation of a class.
4249  * return: class structure
4250  * oid(in):
4251  * record(in): disk record
4252  * Note:
4253  * It is imperitive that garbage collection be disabled during this
4254  * operation.
4255  * This is because the structure being built may contain pointers
4256  * to MOPs but it has not itself been attached to its own MOP yet so it
4257  * doesn't serve as a gc root. Make sure the caller
4258  * calls ws_cache() immediately after we return so the new object
4259  * gets attached as soon as possible. We must also have already
4260  * allocated the MOP in the caller so that we don't get one of the
4261  * periodic gc's when we attempt to allocate a new MOP.
4262  * This dependency should be isolated in a ws_ function called by
4263  * the locator.
4264  */
4265 MOBJ
4266 tf_disk_to_class (OID * oid, RECDES * record)
4267 {
4268  OR_BUF orep, *buf;
4269  unsigned int repid, chn;
4270  /* declare volatile to prevent reg optimization */
4271  MOBJ volatile class_;
4272  int rc = NO_ERROR;
4273 
4274  assert (oid != NULL && !OID_ISNULL (oid));
4275 
4276  /* should we assume this ? */
4277  if (!tf_Metaclass_class.mc_n_variable)
4278  {
4279  tf_compile_meta_classes ();
4280  }
4281 
4282  class_ = NULL;
4283 
4284  buf = &orep;
4285  or_init (buf, record->data, record->length);
4286  buf->error_abort = 1;
4287 
4288  switch (_setjmp (buf->env))
4289  {
4290  case 0:
4291  /* offset size */
4292  assert (OR_GET_OFFSET_SIZE (buf->ptr) == BIG_VAR_OFFSET_SIZE);
4293 
4294  repid = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
4295  repid = repid & ~OR_OFFSET_SIZE_FLAG;
4296  assert (((char) (repid >> OR_MVCC_FLAG_SHIFT_BITS) & OR_MVCC_FLAG_MASK) == 0);
4297  chn = or_get_int (buf, &rc);
4298 
4299  if (oid_is_root (oid))
4300  {
4301  class_ = (MOBJ) disk_to_root (buf);
4302  }
4303  else
4304  {
4305  class_ = (MOBJ) disk_to_class (buf, (SM_CLASS **) (&class_));
4306  if (class_ != NULL)
4307  {
4308  ((SM_CLASS *) class_)->repid = repid;
4309  }
4310  }
4311 
4312  if (class_ != NULL)
4313  {
4314  ((SM_CLASS *) class_)->header.ch_obj_header.chn = chn;
4315  }
4316  break;
4317 
4318  default:
4319  /*
4320  * make sure to clear the class that was being created,
4321  * an appropriate error will have been set
4322  */
4323  if (class_ != NULL)
4324  {
4325  classobj_free_class ((SM_CLASS *) class_);

4338 /*
4339  * tf_class_to_disk - creates the disk representation of a class.
4340  * return: zero for success, non-zero if errors
4341  * classobj(in): pointer to class structure
4342  * record(out): disk record
4343  * Note:
4344  * If the record was not large enough for the class, resulting in
4345  * the or_overflow error, this function returns the required size of the
4346  * record as a negative number.
4347  */
4348 TF_STATUS
4349 tf_class_to_disk (MOBJ classobj, RECDES * record)
4350 {
4351  OR_BUF orep, *buf;
4352  /* prevent reg optimization which hoses longmp */
4353  SM_CLASS *volatile class_;
4354  volatile int expected_size;
4355  SM_CLASS_HEADER *header;
4356  int chn;
4357  TF_STATUS status;
4358  int rc = 0;
4359  volatile int prop_free = 0;
4360  int repid;
4361 
4362  /* should we assume this ? */
4363  if (!tf_Metaclass_class.mc_n_variable)
4364  {
4365  tf_compile_meta_classes ();
4366  }
4367 
4368  /*
4369  * don't worry about deferred fixup for classes, we don't usually have
4370  * many temporary OIDs in classes.
4371  */
4372  buf = &orep;
4373  or_init (buf, record->data, record->area_size);
4374  buf->error_abort = 1;
4375 
4376  class_ = (SM_CLASS *) classobj;
4377 
4378  header = (SM_CLASS_HEADER *) classobj;
4379  if (header->ch_type != SM_META_ROOT)
4380  {
4381  /* put all default_expr values in attribute properties */
4382  rc = tf_attribute_default_expr_to_property (class_->attributes);
4383  }
4384 
4385  /*
4386  * test - this isn't necessary but we've been having a class size related
4387  * bug that I want to try to catch - take this out when we're sure
4388  */
4389  if (class_ == (SM_CLASS *) (&sm_Root_class))
4390  {
4391  expected_size = root_size (classobj);
4392  }
4393  else
4394  {
4395  expected_size = tf_class_size (classobj);
4396  }
4397 
4398  /* if anything failed this far, no need to save stack context, return code will be handled in the switch below */
4399  if (rc == NO_ERROR)
4400  {
4401  rc = _setjmp (buf->env);
4402  }
4403 
4404  switch (rc)
4405  {
4406  case 0:
4407  status = TF_SUCCESS;
4408 
4409  /* representation id, offset size */
4410  repid = class_->repid;
4411  assert (((char) (repid >> OR_MVCC_FLAG_SHIFT_BITS) & OR_MVCC_FLAG_MASK) == 0);
4412  OR_SET_VAR_OFFSET_SIZE (repid, BIG_VAR_OFFSET_SIZE); /* 4byte */
4413 
4414  chn = class_->header.ch_obj_header.chn + 1;
4415  class_->header.ch_obj_header.chn = chn;
4416 
4417  /* The header size of a class record in the same like non-MVCC case. */
4418  or_put_int (buf, repid);
4419  or_put_int (buf, chn);
4420 
4421  if (header->ch_type == SM_META_ROOT)
4422  {
4423  root_to_disk (buf, (ROOT_CLASS *) class_);
4424  }
4425  else
4426  {
4427  assert (class_->repid == (repid & ~OR_OFFSET_SIZE_FLAG));
4428  class_to_disk (buf, (SM_CLASS *) class_);
4429  }
4430 
4431  record->length = CAST_BUFLEN (buf->ptr - buf->buffer);
4432 
4433  /* sanity test, this sets an error only so we can see it if it happens */
4434  if (record->length != expected_size)
4435  {
4436  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TF_SIZE_MISMATCH, 2, expected_size, record->length);
4437  or_abort (buf);
4438  }
4439 
4440  /* fprintf(stdout, "Saved class in %d bytes\n", record->length); */
4441  break;
4442 
4443  /*
4444  * if the longjmp status was anything other than ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW,
4445  * it represents an error condition and er_set will have been called
4446  */
4447 
4448  case ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW:
4449  status = TF_OUT_OF_SPACE;
4450  record->length = -expected_size;
4451  break;
4452 
4453  default:
4454  status = TF_ERROR;
4455  break;
4456 
4457  }
4458 
4459  /* restore properties */
4460  if (((SM_CLASS_HEADER *) classobj)->ch_type != SM_META_ROOT && class_->partition)
4461  {
4462  if (prop_free)
4463  {
4464  classobj_free_prop (class_->properties);
4465  class_->properties = NULL;
4466  }
4467  }
4468 
4469  buf->error_abort = 0;
4470  return (status);
4471 }

4600

4602  assert (default_expr->default_expr_op == T_TO_CHAR);
4603  db_make_int (&value, (int) T_TO_CHAR);

4605

4607  db_make_int (&value, default_expr->default_expr_type);

4609

4626  pr_clear_value (&default_expr_value);
4627 
4628  }

4630  {

4632  db_make_int (&default_expr_value, default_expr->default_expr_type);

4634  }
4635  }

4658  }
4659  else if (attr->properties != NULL)
4660  {
4661  /* make sure property is unset for existing attributes */
4662  classobj_drop_prop (attr->properties, "update_default");

4707 /*
4708  * tf_pack_set - transforms a DB_SET into its disk representation.
4709  * return: error code
4710  * set(in): set to pack
4711  * buffer(out): destination buffer
4712  * buffer_size(in): maximum length of buffer
4713  * actual_bytes(out): number of bytes used or required
4714  * Note:
4715  * If the set will fit within the buffer_size, no error is returned and
4716  * actual_bytes is set to the number of bytes used.
4717  * If the set will not fit in the buffer, ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW is returned
4718  * and actual_bytes is set to the number of bytes that are required
4719  * to pack this set.
4720  * Other errors may occur as the set is examined.
4721  */
4722 int
4723 tf_pack_set (DB_SET * set, char *buffer, int buffer_size, int *actual_bytes)
4724 {
4725  OR_BUF orep, *buf;
4726  int error;
4727  DB_VALUE value;
4728 
4729  if (set == NULL || set->set == NULL)
4730  {
4731  if (actual_bytes != NULL)
4732  {
4733  *actual_bytes = 0;
4734  }
4735  return NO_ERROR;
4736  }
4737 
4738  /* set up a transformation buffer, may want to do deferred fixup here ? */
4739  buf = &orep;
4740  or_init (buf, buffer, buffer_size);
4741  buf->error_abort = 1;
4742 
4743  switch (_setjmp (buf->env))
4744  {
4745  case 0:
4746  error = NO_ERROR;
4747 
4748  /*
4749  * Doesn't matter which set function we pick, all the types are the same.
4750  * Don't have to pass in domain either since the type will be
4751  * self-describing.
4752  */
4753  db_make_set (&value, set);
4754  (*(tp_Set.writeval)) (buf, &value);
4755 
4756  if (actual_bytes != NULL)
4757  {
4758  *actual_bytes = (int) (buf->ptr - buf->buffer);
4759  }
4760  break;
4761 
4762  /*
4763  * something happened, if it was ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW, return
4764  * the desired size as a negative number
4765  */
4766 
4767  case ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW:
4768  error = ER_TF_BUFFER_OVERFLOW;
4769  if (actual_bytes != NULL)
4770  {
4771  DB_VALUE value;
4772  db_make_set (&value, set);
4773  *actual_bytes = (*(tp_Set.lengthval)) (&value, 1);
4774  }
4775  break;
4776 
4777  default:
4778  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4779  error = er_errid ();
4780  break;
4781  }
4782  buf->error_abort = 0;
4783 
4784  return (error);
4785 }
4786 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
